info.senderName: NWS Sioux Falls (Southeastern SD, Southwestern MN, and Northwestern IA)
info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 26 at 8:56AM CST until January 26 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Sioux Falls
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. * WHERE...Lincoln, Lyon and Murray Counties. * WHEN...Until 3 PM CST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Some patchy blowing and drifting snow is also possible in locations that have a sufficient fresh snowcover. This may lead to brief and localized reductions in visibility.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
